article.headline: St. Francis, NY 63, Hartford 60
article.story: NEW YORK -- Ricky Cadell hit a 3-pointer with 4 seconds left to lift St. Francis (N.Y.) to a 63-60 win over Hartford on Tuesday night. With just less than 2 minutes remaining in the game, Clayton Brothers scooped up a loose ball in the paint and put it in off the glass, giving Hartford a 60-58 lead. The Hawks would not score again, setting up Cadell's game-winning shot. With the Terriers (3-5) up by the final margin, Andres Torres drove up the floor and dished it to Morgan Sabia. With a hand in his face, the center attempted a 3 at the buzzer that bounced off the rim. Cadell paced the Terriers with 19 points, including a 5-for-11 performance from 3-point range. Akeem Bennett added 15 points, while Kayode Ayeni and Stefan Perunicic had 10 apiece. Sabia led the Hawks (2-8), who have lost six straight, with 20 points and Joe Zeglinski added 18.
